/*
Personal Portfolio - Single-file React component (Tailwind CSS)

How to use:
1. Create a React app (Vite or Create React App). Example (Vite):
   npm create vite@latest my-portfolio -- --template react
   cd my-portfolio
   npm install

2. Install and configure Tailwind CSS (follow Tailwind docs). Minimal commands:
   npm install -D tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer
   npx tailwindcss init -p

   Add to tailwind.config.js:
   module.exports = {
     content: ["./index.html", "./src/**/*.{js,jsx,ts,tsx}"],
     theme: { extend: {} },
     plugins: [],
   }

   Put this in src/index.css (or App.css):
   @tailwind base;
   @tailwind components;
   @tailwind utilities;

3. Save this file as src/PersonalPortfolio.jsx and import it in src/App.jsx:
   import PersonalPortfolio from "./PersonalPortfolio";
   export default function App(){ return <PersonalPortfolio/> }

4. Run the app: npm run dev (Vite) or npm start (CRA)

Notes:
- This is a fully client-side component that uses Tailwind classes. No external UI library is required.
- Replace placeholder text, images and project links with your content.
- If you want a static HTML version instead, ask and I will provide one.
*/

